ittee files, political campaign files, and social files. There are four series. The Early Years Series consists of items dating before Johnston’s election to the Senate. The U.S. Senate, Political, and Social Series reflect the United States Senate career of Johnston and his staff. The U.S. Senate Series consists of Johnston’s personal and Senate office files. The Political Series consists of Johnston’s campaign files and state and national political files. The Social Series consists of Mardi Gras files and memorabilia. Finding aid available online.","recordType":["Papers"],"recordLocation":{"name":"Louisiana and Lower Mississippi Valley Collections","location":{"addressLocality":"Baton Rouge","addressRegion":"LA"},"parentRecordLocation":{"name":"Louisiana State University","url":"http://www.lib.lsu.edu/special/","location":{"addressLocality":"Baton Rouge","addressRegion":"LA"}}}},{"name":"1996-1997. 45 interviews with various associates. Finding aid available online.","recordType":["Oral history"],"recordLocation":{"name":"Louisiana and Lower Mississippi Valley Collections","location":{"addressLocality":"Baton Rouge","addressRegion":"LA"},"parentRecordLocation":{"name":"Louisiana State University","url":"http://www.lib.lsu.edu/special/","location":{"addressLocality":"Baton Rouge","addressRegion":"LA"}}}},{"name":"1 letter (1974) from Johnston giving details of his move to Washington, DC and immediate impressions of the Senate in Robert DeBlieus collection, 1750s - 1970s.","recordType":["Papers"],"recordLocation":{"name":"Eugene P. Watson Memorial Library","location":{"addressLocality":"Natchitoches","addressRegion":"LA"},"parentRecordLocation":{"name":"Northwestern State University of Louisiana","location":{"addressLocality":"Natchitoches","addressRegion":"LA"}}}}]}
